prompt: Breathing grey-walled dream room, Alice sharp-edged at a static window, your papers on a desk mutating colors and words; ANTIBOY’s masked shadow grins behind you as your floating subtitles read “I understand” while hidden text confesses “it hurts.”
Crack the mask’s jawline into a fault of light; behind it, let the shadow wear your exact face forward while your own flickers half-invisible—Alice now sees only the false you.
Remove the cracked mask fragment from the jaw; reveal bruise-coloured wound on chest, softly glowing with each shared inhale.
